# Vibe-rs build and iteration (for AI assistants)

This repo is a **Cargo workspace** with three crates. **Scope builds** to what you changed‚Äîdo not default to `cargo build` for the whole workspace unless you need an integration check.

## Crates

| Crate | Role | Heavy deps |
|-------|------|------------|
| `vibe_core` | Shared protocol, `TileKey`, world/tile math | `serde`, `postcard`, `glam` |
| `vibe_sim` | Headless server (`vibe_sim` binary) | `tokio`, `rusqlite`, `refinery` ‚Äî **no Bevy** |
| `viberfox` | Bevy client (`viberfox` binary) | **Bevy** + atmosphere ‚Äî slowest crate |

## Preferred commands

- **Verify types after editing shared code**: `cargo check -p vibe_core`
- **Server / networking / DB only**: `cargo check -p vibe_sim` (much faster than pulling Bevy)
- **Game client**: `cargo check -p viberfox` or `cargo run -p viberfox`
- **Touched `vibe_core` and want dependents**: `cargo check -p vibe_sim -p viberfox` (still skip unrelated members when possible)

Avoid `cargo build` without `-p` when a scoped `cargo check -p ‚Ä¶` is enough (agents often only need `check`).

## Faster client iteration (optional)

For **local dev** when iterating on `viberfox` gameplay/UI, Bevy can link as a dylib:

```bash
cargo run -p viberfox --features fast-dev
```

Do **not** use `fast-dev` for `--release` or distributable binaries.

## Dev profiles (root `Cargo.toml`)

Follow [Bevy‚Äôs setup guide](https://bevy.org/learn/quick-start/getting-started/setup/) in spirit; defaults favor **faster rebuilds** over the book‚Äôs heaviest option.

- **Bevy** uses a **slim feature set** (3D + glTF + animation + windowing)‚Äînot full `default`. Re‚Äëenable features in `[workspace.dependencies]` if needed.
- **`dev` (default):** workspace crates **`opt-level = 1`**; dependencies **`opt-level = 0`** (book recommends O3 on `*` for playable debug‚Äîthat is available as **`--profile dev-bevy`**).
- **`split-debuginfo = "unpacked"`** on Linux speeds incremental **links**.
- **Fast compiles:** `cargo run -p viberfox --features fast-dev` ([dynamic linking](https://bevy.org/learn/quick-start/getting-started/setup/#dynamic-linking)); **lld/mold** in `.cargo/config.toml`.
- Do not reintroduce `codegen-units = 1` on all deps without a reason.

## Linker

`.cargo/config.toml` uses **clang + lld** on `x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu`. If linking is still a bottleneck, **mold** is often faster (`fuse-ld=mold`); see comments in that file.

